hey guys i'm new at this what does seeding and leeching mean?

@LIMESTONE081 

Seeds have the complete file (100% of the data) and are actively sharing ... peers are downloading the file and have part of it and usually are sharing pieces also ...When a peer obtains 100% of the data, that peer automatically becomes a Seed.... high numbers of each are best for speed ... low numbers of seeds and high peers will make it slow .. low numbers on each will make it slow ......
